# Statistical Analysis

```{r glmm-setup, include=FALSE}
glmm <- readRDS("~/Desktop/SP26_data/behavioral_output/glmm/glmm_results.rds")
GLMM_FIGS <- "~/Desktop/SP26_data/behavioral_output/glmm"

fmt_p_apa <- function(x) ifelse(x < .001, "< .001",
                                sub("^0", "", sprintf("= %.3f", x)))
fmt_chi <- function(x) sprintf("%.2f", x)

get_nmc <- function(model_name, effect_name) {
  glmm$nmc_all |>
    filter(model == model_name, effect == effect_name) |>
    slice(1)
}
```

## Methods

Accuracy and reaction time data from the pre- and post-test phases were analyzed using mixed-effects models fit with the `lme4` package [@bates2015]. **Accuracy** (binary) was modeled with a generalized linear mixed model with a binomial family and logit link. **Reaction time** on correct trials was modeled with a linear mixed-effects model using a reciprocal transformation (1/RT, i.e., "speed"); this transformation was selected following Box-Cox analysis, which identified λ ≈ −0.7 as the optimal power transformation (95% CI: -0.8 to -0.6), encompassing the reciprocal (λ = -1; Ratcliff, 1993). Predicted speeds are back-transformed to RT in milliseconds for interpretation.

Both models included `group` (L1, L2), `phase` (pre, post), their two-way interaction, and a main effect of `condition` (six levels) as population-level (fixed) effects. The random-effects structure included by-participant random intercepts and slopes for `phase`, and by-item random intercepts [@barr2013].

**Training-phase accuracy** was modeled with a growth-curve GLMM: `group` × standardized trial number as fixed effects, with by-participant random intercepts and slopes for trial.

All categorical predictors were sum-coded so that each coefficient represents a deviation from the grand mean. Trial number in the training model was standardized (mean-centered, divided by 1 SD). Models were fit using the `bobyqa` optimizer.

Model assumptions were assessed via scaled residual diagnostics with the `DHARMa` package. For the RT model, residual diagnostics indicated adequate dispersion (statistic = 0.95, p = .53) and a nearly linear QQ-plot following Box-Cox transformation. Although the Kolmogorov-Smirnov test indicated residual non-uniformity, this is a known sensitivity issue at large sample sizes [~13,000 trials; @schmidt2018]; visual inspection of QQ-plots showed only mild deviations in the extreme tails.

The significance of each fixed effect was evaluated via nested model comparisons: each effect was dropped from the full model and the reduced model was compared to the full model with a likelihood ratio test. Marginal and conditional R² were calculated following Nakagawa & Schielzeth [-@nakagawa2013] using the `MuMIn` package. Decision rule: α = .05.

## Results

```{r glmm-fit-table}
library(knitr)
kable(glmm$r2_summary,
      caption = "Goodness of fit for each model.",
      col.names = c("Model", "Marginal R²", "Conditional R²"))
```

### Accuracy (testing phase)

```{r acc-results, results='asis'}
nmc_group <- get_nmc("accuracy", "group")
nmc_phase <- get_nmc("accuracy", "phase")
nmc_int   <- get_nmc("accuracy", "group:phase")
nmc_cond  <- get_nmc("accuracy", "cond_name")

cat(sprintf(
"Accuracy differed reliably as a function of group [χ²(%d) = %s, *p* %s] and phase [χ²(%d) = %s, *p* %s]. The group × phase interaction was %s [χ²(%d) = %s, *p* %s]. The main effect of condition was %s [χ²(%d) = %s, *p* %s].\n\n",
nmc_group$df, fmt_chi(nmc_group$chisq), fmt_p_apa(nmc_group$p),
nmc_phase$df, fmt_chi(nmc_phase$chisq), fmt_p_apa(nmc_phase$p),
ifelse(nmc_int$p < .05, "significant", "not significant"),
nmc_int$df,   fmt_chi(nmc_int$chisq),   fmt_p_apa(nmc_int$p),
ifelse(nmc_cond$p < .05, "significant", "not significant"),
nmc_cond$df,  fmt_chi(nmc_cond$chisq),  fmt_p_apa(nmc_cond$p)
))
```

```{r acc-fixed-table}
glmm$fixed_all |>
  filter(model == "accuracy") |>
  select(-model) |>
  kable(caption = "Accuracy model: fixed-effect estimates (log-odds scale).",
        col.names = c("Term", "β", "SE", "CI low", "CI high", "p"),
        digits = 3)
```

```{r acc-predicted}
glmm$interp_acc |>
  select(group, phase, predicted_pct, CI_pct) |>
  kable(caption = "Accuracy model: predicted probabilities by group and phase.",
        col.names = c("Group", "Phase", "Predicted", "95% CI"))
```

### Reaction time (testing phase, correct trials)

```{r rt-results, results='asis'}
nmc_group <- get_nmc("rt", "group")
nmc_phase <- get_nmc("rt", "phase")
nmc_int   <- get_nmc("rt", "group:phase")
nmc_cond  <- get_nmc("rt", "cond_name")

cat(sprintf(
"Reaction time on correct trials differed reliably as a function of group [χ²(%d) = %s, *p* %s] and phase [χ²(%d) = %s, *p* %s]. The group × phase interaction was %s [χ²(%d) = %s, *p* %s]. The main effect of condition was %s [χ²(%d) = %s, *p* %s].\n\n",
nmc_group$df, fmt_chi(nmc_group$chisq), fmt_p_apa(nmc_group$p),
nmc_phase$df, fmt_chi(nmc_phase$chisq), fmt_p_apa(nmc_phase$p),
ifelse(nmc_int$p < .05, "significant", "not significant"),
nmc_int$df,   fmt_chi(nmc_int$chisq),   fmt_p_apa(nmc_int$p),
ifelse(nmc_cond$p < .05, "significant", "not significant"),
nmc_cond$df,  fmt_chi(nmc_cond$chisq),  fmt_p_apa(nmc_cond$p)
))
```

```{r rt-fixed-table}
glmm$fixed_all |>
  filter(model == "rt") |>
  select(-model) |>
  kable(caption = "RT model: fixed-effect estimates (1/RT scale; positive = faster).",
        col.names = c("Term", "β", "SE", "CI low", "CI high", "p"),
        digits = 3)
```

```{r rt-predicted}
glmm$interp_rt |>
  select(group, phase, predicted_ms, CI_ms) |>
  kable(caption = "RT model: predicted RT by group and phase (back-transformed from 1/RT).",
        col.names = c("Group", "Phase", "Predicted", "95% CI"))
```

### Training (growth curve)

```{r train-results, results='asis'}
nmc_group <- get_nmc("training", "group")
nmc_trial <- get_nmc("training", "trial_z")
nmc_int   <- get_nmc("training", "group:trial_z")

cat(sprintf(
"Training accuracy increased reliably with trial [χ²(%d) = %s, *p* %s] and differed by group [χ²(%d) = %s, *p* %s]. The group × trial interaction was %s [χ²(%d) = %s, *p* %s], indicating that L1 and L2 speakers %s during training.\n\n",
nmc_trial$df, fmt_chi(nmc_trial$chisq), fmt_p_apa(nmc_trial$p),
nmc_group$df, fmt_chi(nmc_group$chisq), fmt_p_apa(nmc_group$p),
ifelse(nmc_int$p < .05, "significant", "not significant"),
nmc_int$df,   fmt_chi(nmc_int$chisq),   fmt_p_apa(nmc_int$p),
ifelse(nmc_int$p < .05, "learned at different rates", "learned at comparable rates")
))
```

```{r train-fixed-table}
glmm$fixed_all |>
  filter(model == "training") |>
  select(-model) |>
  kable(caption = "Training model: fixed-effect estimates (log-odds scale).",
        col.names = c("Term", "β", "SE", "CI low", "CI high", "p"),
        digits = 3)
```

